        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 2 at 5:48AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>Patchy areas of fog have developed this morning. Some of this fog
could be locally dense in spots with visibilities below a 1/2
mile. Motorists should prepare for sharp changes in visibility,
allow for extra travel time, and use low beam lights. The fog
should dissipate by mid-morning.
</description>
